<figcaption>COVID-19 translation challenge. Image from <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/covid-language-translation-problem/">WIRED</a>.</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p>“In the long run, Translators Without Borders aims to help with this tech problem too, through a project known as the Translation Initiative for Covid-19 (TICO-19). TWB is working with researchers at Carnegie Mellon and a who’s who of major tech companies including Microsoft, Google, Facebook, and Amazon (with the notable exception of Apple) to translate Covid-related materials in 36 languages through these companies’ networks of translators (and on their dimes).”</p>
<p>TICO-19 link is in the first comment.</p>
