</figure>
</div>
<p>Halcin: the first antibiotic discovered with AI/DNN.</p>
<p>“First, we trained a deep neural network model to predict growth inhibition of Escherichia coli using a collection of 2,335 molecules. Second, we applied the resulting model to several discrete chemical libraries, comprising &gt;107 million molecules, to identify potential lead compounds with activity against E. coli. After ranking the compounds according to the model’s predicted score, we lastly selected a list of candidates based on a pre-specified prediction score threshold, chemical structure, and availability.”</p>
